In CT disconnecting a charger from another persons car while it's charging without their permission is considered damaged to personal property and is punishable by law.

Owner paid for Damages rather than Pressing Charges for this and having them arrested.

comments: Mar 2, 2020check_circlecancelaccess_timeinfoMyTH solarpowerChevrolet Bolt EV 2017 J-1772  Volts  Amps  Kilowatts In order to come back to a fully-charged car waiting for you curbside by the station, here's what to do: Call the valet service (203-584-6332) before you first arrive and ask if they would be willing to charge your EV in the garage and then move it to their normal lot.  When you get to Union Station, drop your car at the curb using the Valet Lane.  Leave your ChargePoint RFID proximity card on the passenger seat and have a quick chat with the valet about how to use it to activate the charger and how many hours it will need to charge (at 6 kW).  Upon return a few days later, call that same valet hotline number from the train while 20 to 30 minutes out, and they will fetch your car.  Cost is $25 per day plus tip.  Note that the valet and the garage are separate businesses, accustomed to working together, and in this scenario, you are a customer of the valet service, not the garage.(edited)  Was this helpful?  driver found this helpful  drivers found this helpful

I had to play with the left (there are four in a row) to finally get it to work.  It took four times before it worked. I think there might be a broken or loose control wire. Try Straightening the cable first before inserting if this is the only available charger. The charger furthest on the right worked the first time. The two in the middle have no power and are dead.  I only charged on each one for 3 minutes and added 2 miles of charge. To use turn the power on and wait. The machine makes noise for 30 seconds and nothing seems to happen (both did this) then it drops the j1772 about 5 feet then stops. You need to manually pull it out the rest of the way and insert into your car.
